<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,152,251]" pageId="14" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,153,179]" pageId="14" pageNumber="91">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Price, A. R. G." box="[325,465,152,179]" pageId="14" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref17861" refString="Price, A. R. G. (1981) Studies on the echinoderm fauna of the western Arabian Gulf. Journal of Natural History, 15, 1 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938100770011" type="journal article" year="1981">Price (1981)</bibRefCitation>
remarked that his eight specimens were intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- A. M. Clark" authorityYear="1968" box="[1177,1388,152,179]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Macrophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="91" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="hirsuta" subSpecies="cheneyi">
<emphasis box="[1177,1200,153,178]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="91">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1215,1388,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="91">hirsuta cheneyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1938" box="[151,286,188,215]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Macrophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="91" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[151,174,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="91">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[188,286,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="91">elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with regard to arm length, arm spines and the shape of dorsal and ventral arm plates. He did not discuss them in his more detailed later treatment (
<bibRefCitation author="Price, A. R. G." box="[620,743,224,251]" pageId="14" pageNumber="91" pagination="28 - 108" refId="ref17950" refString="Price, A. R. G. (1983) Echinoderms of Saudi Arabia: Echinoderms of the Arabian Gulf Coast of Saudi Arabia. In: Wittmer, W. &amp; Buttiker, W. (Eds.), Fauna of Saudi Arabia. Karger Libri, Basel, pp. 28 - 108." type="book chapter" year="1983">Price 1983</bibRefCitation>
) and so their identity remains uncertain.
</paragraph>
